post_text: Central Square School District is happy to share our information, our triumphs and our memories with you on Facebook. We appreciate the supportive and constructive Facebook comments that you continue to provide. As we cannot monitor all comments on Facebook, we want to remind you that if you have questions or concerns, the quickest and most effective way to get a response is to call or email someone in the District. Please continue to enjoy our page! :)

post_text:
On this day...19 years ago…246 people awoke and prepared for their morning flights. 2,606 people awoke to report for a typical workday. 343 firefighters awoke for their morning shift. 60 police officers awoke for morning patrol. 8 paramedics awoke for their morning shifts of saving lives. None of them saw past 10:00am that morning, on Sept 11, 2001. :(

In one single moment life can change and may never be the same. As you live and enjoy the breaths you take today and before you go to sleep, kiss the ones you love, snuggle them a little tighter, and never take one second of life for granted.
We will never forget! #CentralSquareRedhawks #RedhawkPride #NeverForget #911

As we continue to work with local organizations to help our families navigate another school year amid the COVID-19 pandemic, we would like to let you know about a great resource for those in need of childcare.

Integrated Community Planning of Oswego County can help you find childcare no matter what your desired type of childcare, hours of need or location. Please call 315-343-2344 for more information on the Child Care Resources & Referral Program or visit their website at https://www.icpoc.org.

post_text:
Words cannot adequately express how disappointed we are to be unable to have a traditional graduation ceremony this year. We hope that this video, in combination with our drive-thru graduation being held at the stadium today, helps to recreate some of the magic that you deserve. Seniors will also receive a copy of this video on a flash drive with your diploma.

We are so very proud of you, your hard work and perserverance in the face of this pandemic. We know you will do great things -- don't forget you will always have a home here! As one we rise, together we soar! #CentralSquareRedhawks #RedhawkPride #PVMProud

It has come to our attention that some of you are still not seeing the messages that we have been sending out. In most cases, these messages have been landing in spam folders. We want to make sure that you are up-to-date on district information, so we are asking everyone to make sure that they have "whitelisted" messages from Central Square School District.

We put together a quick reference guide on how to do this for both Yahoo and Gmail accounts here: https://www.cssd.org/cms/lib/NY50000232/Centricity/Domain/4/Spam_Filter_Resolution.pdf

Also, please make sure that your primary contact information is updated in SchoolTool, as this is the contact information we use to send out all email/text blasts.

post_text:
CSSD voting ballots are arriving today. https://tinyurl.com/Voting-ballots-arriving

Voting ballots have arrived at many of the homes in the Central Square School District today, and if your ballot did not arrive today, I am sure that it will arrive in tomorrow’s mail. NTS, the company we use for the voting process, mailed an absentee ballot to the approximate 15,000 eligible voters residing in our school district.

As mentioned in a previous parent/guardian letter, the District will have a locked box to drop off your ballot, for anyone that would rather personally submit your ballot than to mail it back. The locked ballot box will be located at the Central Square Intermediate building, at 68 School Drive in Central Square on Monday, June 8 from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. and Tuesday, June 9 from 9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m. It will be right inside the front door and the District Clerk will be there to oversee this
process.

 Please make sure you fill out both the ballot and envelope completely, and
sign/date the return envelope.

 All ballots must be received by 5:00 p.m. on June 9, 2020.

post_text:
Attention Seniors and Senior Parents/Guardians -- Class of 2020 yard sign pick-up is tomorrow!

First and foremost, we hope that you and your families are healthy and well. We are proud of all of you and your efforts throughout your high school career.

In an effort to continue to show community and school support, yard signs have been purchased and are available for each of our 2020 Seniors!

Senior Sign Pick-up Details:
When: Friday, May 1st, 2020
Time: 1pm-3pm
Where: PVM Student Parking Lot via Tucker Ave
Details: When you enter the student parking lot via Tucker Ave, a staff member will provide you with a sign. Please maintain safe driving habits and do not exit your vehicle--we must maintain strict social distancing guidelines. After receiving your sign (and it is safe to drive), continue driving straight to exit the parking lot via Rt. 12.

When you arrive home, we encourage you to proudly display your sign in your yard or a front window!! Congratulations!!!! 👏😀 #PVMProud #ClassOf2020

post_text:
With more families needing food because COVID-19 has left many unemployed, our community stepped up in a big way with staff and community members donating over $50,000 worth of food in just three hours.

Our School District encompasses 3 counties and all of our individual communities came together in this herculean effort. No families in our District will go without food. This is a special
place!

Our District’s mission is to “empower all students to excel as citizens in a changing world,” and this is a perfect illustration of
that, and a wonderful lesson that all students will benefit from.

The world literally changed in a month, and we have excelled!!! 🥰🥫🥪

post_text:
REDHAWK REMINDER: Tomorrow starts PVM's Virtual Spirit Week (April 6th through 10th)!!

School might be closed, but we can still show our school spirit! Each day PVM will collect pictures you send and share them on social media by tagging it #pvmproud.

Themes for days of the week will be:

Monday, April 6 - Positive Message Day! Share a positive message and share it with the community. Make a poster and put it in your window. Show us your message!

Tuesday, April 7 - Tropical Tuesday - Wear some of your tropical floral prints or bright colors!

Wednesday, April 8 - Hats off to emergency workers! Wear a hat or crazy hat!

Thursday, April 9 - Tie Dye Day - wear your favorite tie dye attire.

Friday, April 10 - Redhawk Pride! Show your support for the wonderful community of Central Square. If you've got Redhawk gear show it off!

Be sure to send us your pictures! Take a picture and tag it #pvmproud or tag us on Twitter:

Mrs. O’Malley- @OMalleyJenn
Mr. Soluri- @Soluri_c
Mr. Villnave- @dvillnave

We can’t wait to see your smiling faces!

post_text: We want you all to know that we understand your frustrations with the uncertainty of this situation. Superintendents do not have the authority to call for a prolonged closure of a school district. That must come from the Governor, the Health Department or the County Executive. We will update you if/when any of these entities authorize such actions to be taken.

DAY 10: Last, but certainly not least, our Superintendent Thomas J. Colabufo was a proud and enthusiastic volunteer when we asked him to tell us what he loves about Central Square. Check out what he had to say!
